can check if the factory is usable at runtime. I also need to consider the Java JVM test with the jvmArgs property to cover the branch and fallback effectively.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test class integration**\\n\\nI'm wondering if it includes test classes, which it should. There's a potential issue if the native image build initializes TraceFactory before the test classes are compiled; this could be problematic since it may not work after compilation. I should consider whether a global property could impact tests or classes outside of the current active context, and it seems related only to the aspectjweaver project. I'll need to write a file to address this.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_XLbLFVV7Vc9zLV559mUQlK1Y|fc_064330bd950863460169f1829cb1e08193952730272ef32437", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.aspectj/aspectjweaver/1.9.7/src/test/java/org_aspectj/aspectjweaver/TraceFactoryTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_aspectj.aspectjweaver;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport org.aspectj.weaver.tools.Trace;\nimport org.aspectj.weaver.tools.TraceFactory;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class TraceFactoryTest {\n    private static final String FACTORY_PROPERTY = \"org.aspectj.tracing.factory\";\n    private static final String FAILING_FACTORY_NAME = TraceFactoryTest.class.getName() + \"$FailingTraceFactory\";\n\n    @Test\n    void fallsBackWhenConfiguredTraceFactoryCannotBeCreated() {\n        String previousFactory = System.getProperty(FACTORY_PROPERTY);\n        System.setProperty(FACTORY_PROPERTY, FAILING_FACTORY_NAME);\n        try {\n            TraceFactory factory = TraceFactory.getTraceFactory();\n            Trace trace = factory.getTrace(TraceFactoryTest.class);\n\n            assertThat(factory).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(factory).isNotInstanceOf(FailingTraceFactory.class);\n            assertThat(trace).isNotNull();\n        } finally {\n            restoreFactoryProperty(previousFactory);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void restoreFactoryProperty(String previousFactory) {\n        if (previousFactory == null) {\n            System.clearProperty(FACTORY_PROPERTY);\n        } else {\n            System.setProperty(FACTORY_PROPERTY, previousFactory);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class FailingTraceFactory extends TraceFactory {\n        public FailingTraceFactory() {\n            throw new IllegalStateException(\"Configured trace factory failure\");\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Trace getTrace(Class clazz) {\n            throw new AssertionError(\"The failing trace factory must not create traces\");\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.aspectj/aspectjweaver/1.9.7/src/test/java/org_aspectj/aspectjweaver/TraceFactoryTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_aspectj.aspectjweaver;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\nimport org.aspectj.weaver.tools.Trace;\\nimport org.aspectj.weaver.tools.TraceFactory;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\npublic class TraceFactoryTest {\\n    private static final String FACTORY_PROPERTY = \\\"org.aspectj.tracing.factory\\\";\\n    private static final String FAILING_FACTORY_NAME = TraceFactoryTest.class.getName() + \\\"$FailingTraceFactory\\\";\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void fallsBackWhenConfiguredTraceFactoryCannotBeCreated() {\\n        String previousFactory = System.getProperty(FACTORY_PROPERTY);\\n        System.setProperty(FACTORY_PROPERTY, FAILING_FACTORY_NAME);\\n        try {\\n            TraceFactory factory = TraceFactory.getTraceFactory();\\n            Trace trace = factory.getTrace(TraceFactoryTest.class);\\n\\n            assertThat(factory).isNotNull();\\n            assertThat(factory).isNotInstanceOf(FailingTraceFactory.class);\\n            assertThat(trace).isNotNull();\\n        } finally {\\n            restoreFactoryProperty(previousFactory);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static void restoreFactoryProperty(String previousFactory) {\\n        if (previousFactory == null) {\\n            System.clearProperty(FACTORY_PROPERTY);\\n        } else {\\n            System.setProperty(FACTORY_PROPERTY, previousFactory);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public static class FailingTraceFactory extends TraceFactory {\\n        public FailingTraceFactory() {\\n            throw new IllegalStateException(\\\"Configured trace factory failure\\\");\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public Trace getTrace(Class clazz) {\\n            throw new AssertionError(\\\"The failing trace factory must not create traces\\\");\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 566, "output": 2882, "cacheRead": 31232, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34680, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777435256634, "responseId": "resp_064330bd950863460169f1827985e08193b60b0fb92ed2ab46"}}
